<br>
Right now, I have all 10 spell sets used up, but I need to reorganize them since there are a few I don't use too often. Anyway, there are the ones I use:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Power Healing:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->This one is just what it says. In order:<br>
<br>
• Complete Healing<br>
• Divine Light<br>
• Remedy<br>
• Celestial Healing<br>
• Word of Restoration<br>
• Pureblood<br>
• Divine Barrier<br>
• Divine Aura<br>
<br>
This is the one I usually have up when I'm in a complete heal chain or something similar, or in a group where I am healing and *only* healing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dungeoning:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This was created in response to the launch of Lost Dungeons of Norrath. It's not terribly different, but here goes:<br>
<br>
• Complete Healing<br>
• Divine Light<br>
• Word of Restoration<br>
• Celestial Healing<br>
• Pureblood<br>
• Remove Curse<br>
• Divine Barrier<br>
• Unswerving Hammer of Faith<br>
<br>
This way I can be ready to cure just about anything. If we're fighting mostly undead, a lot of times I'll swap out Remove Curse for Yaulp V and jump in with my hammer. Otherwise, I just cast my hammer pet to help out a bit.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Soloing nuke/stun:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This is my &quot;fun&quot; spell set, I use it in combination with Soloing dotting undead below when I am hunting on my own in places like Maiden's Eye or Akheva.<br>
<br>
• Celestial Healing<br>
• Pacify<br>
• Judgement<br>
• Paralyzing Earth<br>
• Sound of Force<br>
• Force<br>
• Divine Barrier<br>
• Gate<br>
<br>
If I end up facing a cleric Xin Thall Centien, I usually root it then run out of range and swap out Gate and Pacify for my other stuns. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Soloing dotting undead:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->Much the same as above, but with the attention squarely focused on dots. <br>
<br>
• Celestial healing<br>
• Pacify<br>
• Paralyzing Earth<br>
• Epitaph of Life<br>
• Sermon of the Righteous<br>
• Turning of the Unnatural<br>
• Divine Barrier<br>
• Stun<br>
<br>
If I get a burning affliction item, stacking the three dots causes 200+ damage a tic, which isn't too bad, and it wears down Xi Vius, skeletal drudges and such fairly nicely.<br>
<br>
So .. what do YOU usually have memorized? If you don't mind sharing, of course. Why and in which situations do you use your spell sets? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
