<br>
So, I have spell sets labeled &quot;Rez, LDON, Ssra AE, Ssra Raid, BOT Tower, BOT move, Duo Factory, Duo Seru, Duo Enc&quot;, etc..  I tend to toss out the ones that in the middle ground and keep the ones I do often and the ones I do rarely.  The often-done are obvious keepers.  The rares I keep to remind me of what tactics I used last time at that encounter.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if you're agonizing over how to setup your memorized lists, this is a quick solution to avoid spending a bunch of time making &quot;perfect spell sets&quot;.  Just memorize sets as you create them for each encounter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phyxious>Phyxious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/03 1:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Different Approaches</span><hr size=1> Interesting reading the different approaches folks have taken, I myself have just a few spell sets.  Buffs, Undead, LiveSolo, Normal, MaxHeal, and KOS (for getting thru KOS areas.)<br>
