<br>
Then I have my three basic combat (02 COMBAT) spells in a set that only uses the three empty slots. I usually have a root, stun, nuke in this set but it evolves over time as I learn and grow.<br>
<br>
I then create other sets that have only those gem slots filled. Special purpose, quick load sets such as my three cursed object spells, or my three best stuns, etc. (04 CURE, 05 OBJECT, 06 STUN...) The sets I use tend to change a little as my play style evolves and I get suggestions from other players.<br>
<br>
When fighting if I need to quickly load disease/poison/curse cures then I can quickly load that set and then return to my regular set for the current situation.<br>
<br>
When I need a quick spell, like gate, I use the right-click spell load in one of the three re-useable slots, and then reload the the spell set to get things back to normal.<br>
<br>
